    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="137"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d137">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.711/111: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-20T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 20, 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>868. Your A–1815, September 1, 8:30 a.m.<note n="34" xml:id="d137fn34">Not
                        printed.</note> The President has allocated to the Department, from the
                    appropriation entitled “Emergency Fund, for the President, National Defense,
                        1942–1944”<note n="35" xml:id="d137fn35">Appropriation Acts, 1942, 1943, and
                        1944; 55 Stat. 682, 813, 818; 56 Stat. 394, 704, 995; 57 Stat. 432.</note>
                    the amount of $150,000 to be expended by the Department in connection with
                    emergencies affecting the national security and defense, for reimbursement to
                    the Government of the Republic of Cuba for all necessary expenses incident to
                    the establishment and maintenance of postal censorship of the mails in Cuba
                    during the fiscal year 1944.</p>
                <pb facs="0161" n="147" xml:id="pg_147"/>
                <p>Formal request for funds for the censorship of the telegraph, cables, and radio
                    in Cuba, including broadcasting, will be submitted to Budget in the very near
                    future.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
